This week I will be summarizing the recent paper by Dr. Shell and Dr. Rossi at Texas A&M University and NASA's JPL [<a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2208.03351.pdf">link</a>]. The paper covers a novel problem of making decisions under periodic observations 

Assumptions:
- Underlying Markovian process
- New observations received at constant and known interval (k)
- No other observations occur between actions

"challenge is sparseness rather than degradation or corruption through random noise"

Contributions:
1) Formally define this novel problem as a stochastic decision problem
2) Derive upper and lower bounds for state-action values 
3) Propose branch-and-bound method that uses (2) to compute exact solutions to the PSO-MDP

Problem can be formulated as PSO-MDP or an equivalent special POMDP 

